  "prompt": "International student: What are my chances to get into MIT?",
  "response": "Getting accepted into MIT as an international student is highly competitive, but it's certainly possible if you meet or exceed their rigorous standards. Here are several key factors that will impact your chances:\n\n1. **Academic Excellence:** MIT is renowned for its rigorous academic standards. You will need to demonstrate exceptional performance in your school coursework, standardized tests (such as SAT or ACT), and any other relevant exams. Aim for top grades in challenging courses, particularly in mathematics and sciences.\n\n2. **Standardized Tests:** While MIT is test-optional through 2023-2024, strong SAT or ACT scores can enhance your application. Additionally, high scores on subject tests, AP exams, or IB exams can be beneficial.\n\n3. **Extracurricular Activities:** MIT looks for students who are not only academically outstanding but also show exceptional involvement in extracurricular activities. Leadership roles, participation in noteworthy projects, competitions, or community service can make a significant difference.\n\n4. **Research and Innovation:** Demonstrating a passion for research, innovation, and problem-solving is crucial. If you've been involved in research projects, internships, or have developed unique solutions to real-world problems, make sure these achievements are highlighted in your application.\n\n5. **Personal Essays:** Your essays are an opportunity to showcase your personality, aspirations, and unique experiences. Spend time crafting thoughtful and genuine responses that reflect who you are and why MIT is the right fit for you.\n\n6. **Recommendation Letters:** Strong recommendations from teachers and mentors who know you well can provide valuable insight into your abilities and character.\n\n7. **Diversity and Fit:** MIT values diversity and is looking for students who will bring unique perspectives to their campus. Highlight your experiences and how they have shaped your worldview and future ambitions.\n\nRemember that admission is holistic, and MIT evaluates applicants based on a combination of these factors. While the acceptance rate for international students is low, crafting a well-rounded and compelling application can improve your chances. Ensure that you meet all the application requirements and deadlines, and make the best case for why MIT is the right place for you.",
